[01:27.85]	For one poor grain or two, to leave unburnt,
[01:31.34]	And still to nose the offence.
[01:33.91]MENENIUS	For one poor grain or two!
[01:36.19]	I am one of those; his mother, wife, his child,
[01:39.76]	And this brave fellow too, we are the grains:
[01:43.32]	You are the musty chaff; and you are smelt
